    <fr:title text="Hermitian matrix">Hermitian matrix</fr:title>
    <fr:taxon>definition</fr:taxon>
  </fr:frontmatter>
  <fr:mainmatter>
    <html:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbf {A} = (a_{ij})]]></fr:tex> be a matrix over <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {C}]]></fr:tex>. We call <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbf {A}]]></fr:tex> <html:dfn>Hermitian</html:dfn> (or <html:dfn>Self-Adjoint</html:dfn>) if it is equal to its complex-conjugate transpose:</html:p>
    <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[a_{ij} = \overline {a_{ji}}]]></fr:tex>
    <html:p>Or equivalently:</html:p>
    <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[\mathbf {A} = \overline {A^{\mathsf {T}}}]]></fr:tex>
  </fr:mainmatter>
